<TITLE> Journalist Arif Rahman dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 20 (bdnews24.com)Journalist Arif Rahman died of a heart attack at Holy Family Hospital in the capital on Wednesday morning. He was 44. A former general secretary of crime reporters' organisation CRAB, he left behind wife and one daughter. Rahman took to journalism in the 1980s and worked for a long time in the daily Ajker Kagoj. After its closure, he joined as chief reporter of the Dainik Karotoa, and then the Bhorer Daak. Home minister Sahara Khatun and state minister for home affairs Tanjim Ahmed, Dhaka Reporters' Unity president Shamim Ahmed and general secretary Pathik Shaha condoled his death. CRAB president Akhtaruzzaman Bablu and general secretary Abu Saleh Akon also condoled the demise. His Namaj-e-Janaza was held at the premises of Dhaka Reporters' Unity at noon. Later, his body was taken to Tithulia of Dhunat in Bogra. He was buried beside his father's grave.
